Metasoma.
0.27 as wide as long, with few setae, ventral carina of petiole present. Hypopygium (
Fig. 144
) with posterior margin strongly angulate; teeth of posterior margin straight, teeth distant each other, almost evenly thick; lateral stalk present, but almost vestigial. Genitalia (
Figs 163–165
) with paramere doble, apical margin in lateral view without concavity, inner margin of ventral arm not angulate in lateral view; basiparamere with apical margin angulate medially; volsella aligned with aedeagus apex; cuspis 0.36 length of apical lobe of aedeagus, 1.40 width of apical lobe of aedeagus; digitus 0.50 length of apical lobe of aedeagus, upper surface spinose; aedeagus with median region as wide as base; apical lobe 0.45 aedeagus length, fold of inner margin present; apex straight.
